@page "/commands/overview-antisnipe"

@layout StandardLayout

<CommandPage DisplayFooter="true">
    <MudHidden Breakpoint="Breakpoint.MdAndUp">
        <CommandPageHeader Title="Anti-Snipe Settings" Typography="Typo.h5" SubTitle="Prevents bidders from swooping in at the final moment to snatch a win." />
    </MudHidden>
    <MudHidden Breakpoint="Breakpoint.MdAndUp" Invert="true">
        <CommandPageHeader Title="Anti-Snipe Settings" SubTitle="Prevents bidders from swooping in at the final moment to snatch a win." />
    </MudHidden>
    <PageContent>
        <PageSection>
            <SectionHeader Title="Configuring Anti-Snipe" HideSectionLink="true">
                <Description>
                    Follow these simple steps to enable the Anti-Snipe option for a more equitable bidding experience.
                </Description>
            </SectionHeader>
            <SectionSubGroups>
                <PageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="Setup">
                        <Description>
                            <div class="d-flex flex-column px-2">
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        Begin by executing the command: <InlineCode>/server settings</InlineCode>
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        From the drop-down, select <InlineCode>Snipe Trigger</InlineCode>.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        From the second drop-down, select the preferred trigger time period. This defines the time frame before an auction closes, during which last-second bids will trigger an extension.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        In the same settings menu, select <InlineCode>Snipe Extension</InlineCode> from the first drop-down
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        In the second drop-down, select the duration that best suites your needs. This determines the additional time that will be added to the auction if a bid is placed during the snipe trigger period.
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        That's it, you're done!
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </PageSection>
            </SectionSubGroups>
        </PageSection>

        <PageSection>
            <SectionHeader Title="How it Works" HideSectionLink="true" />
            <SectionSubGroups>
                <PageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="Understanding how Anti-Snipe Functions">
                        <Description>
                            <div class="d-flex flex-column px-2">
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        <strong>Current Time</strong>: 12:03
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        <strong>Scheduled End</strong>: 12:05 (in 2 minutes)
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        <strong>Snipe Trigger</strong>: 5 minutes
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                                <MudBadge Color="Color.Primary" Dot="true" Bordered="true" Origin="Origin.CenterLeft">
                                    <div class="pl-4 mt-2">
                                        <strong>Snipe Extension</strong>: 10 minutes
                                    </div>
                                </MudBadge>
                            </div>
                            <br/>

                            Imagine a scenario where a user places a bid when there are only 2 minutes left until the auction ends. 
                            Normally, the auction would end at <strong>12:05</strong>. However, with the Anti-Snipe option activated,
                            the auction end time is <strong>extended</strong> by the snipe extension duration (10 minutes in this case).
                            This means that the new Auction End time is <strong>12:13</strong> (10 minutes from the current time).<br/><br/>

                            Even though the scheduled end date remains unchanged, the actual expiration time gets updated to accommodate the additional time.
                        </Description>
                    </SectionHeader>
                </PageSection>
            </SectionSubGroups>
        </PageSection>

        <PageSection>
            <SectionHeader Title="A Word of Caution">
                <Description>
                    While the Anti-Snipe option ensures fairness and excitement, it's essential to be mindful of potential extensions. 
                    In some cases, auctions could be prolonged well beyond the initially expected end time due to continuous bidding within the snipe trigger period.<br/><br/>

                    By following these guidelines and using the Anti-Snipe option strategically, you'll enhance the bidding process for all participants and increase the thrill of every auction.<br/> <br/>
                    Happy bidding!
                </Description>
            </SectionHeader>
        </PageSection>

        <PageSection>
            <SectionSubGroups>
                <PageSection>
                    <SectionHeader Title="Additional Details" HideTitle="true" />
                    <div class="d-flex flex-row flex-wrap mud-width-full">
                        <MudList Clickable="true" Class="flex-grow-1 flex-shrink-0 mud-paper-outlined rounded py-0 ma-2">
                            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.VerifiedUser" IconColor="Color.Primary" Class="pl-6" Href="commands/overview-roles">
                                <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">Access Roles</MudText>
                                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Control who can buy/sell and more...</MudText>
                            </MudListItem>
                        </MudList>
                        <MudList Clickable="true" Class="flex-grow-1 flex-shrink-0 mud-paper-outlined rounded py-0 ma-2">
                            <MudListItem Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.AutoAwesomeMosaic" IconColor="Color.Tertiary" Class="pl-6" Href="commands/overview-showrooms">
                                <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">Showrooms</MudText>
                                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Understing Showroom options!</MudText>
                            </MudListItem>
                        </MudList>
                    </div>
                </PageSection>
            </SectionSubGroups>
        </PageSection>
    </PageContent>
</CommandPage>